title: Google\Cloud\Gaming\V1\KubernetesClusterState
name: KubernetesClusterState
description:
The state of the Kubernetes cluster.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gaming.v1.KubernetesClusterState

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.agones_version_installed
params.description: Output only. The version of Agones currently installed in the registered Kubernetes cluster.

params.name: data.kubernetes_version_installed
params.description: Output only. The version of Kubernetes that is currently used in the registered Kubernetes cluster (as detected by the Cloud Game Servers service).

params.name: data.installation_state
params.description: Output only. The state for the installed versions of Agones/Kubernetes.

params.name: data.version_installed_error_message
params.description: Output only. The detailed error message for the installed versions of Agones/Kubernetes.

params.name: data.provider
params.description: Output only. The cloud provider type reported by the first node's providerID in the list of nodes on the Kubernetes endpoint. On Kubernetes platforms that support zero-node clusters (like GKE-on-GCP), the provider type will be empty.

params.name: data.agones_version_targeted
params.description: Output only. The version of Agones that is targeted to be installed in the cluster.
